# Cursor INDEX-ignore (not access-ignore).
#
# These paths are excluded from the Cursor *index* so per-run / generated
# churn stops eating the index budget, but — unlike `.cursorignore` — they
# stay readable by the agent via Read / scripts/verify_run.py when a specific
# artefact actually needs inspecting.
#
# Rationale: every builder run drops generated TSX + 8 artefacts under
# data/runs/<runId>/, plus embedding vectors and a .generated/<siteId>/ tree.
# Re-indexing that on every change pollutes code search with no editing value.
#
# data/prompt-inputs/ is intentionally NOT listed: it is small canonical JSON
# (the per-version Project Input snapshots) that is useful to search.

data/runs/
data/versions/
data/embedding-index/
.generated/
